  "text": "Bootstrapping, or Weakly and semi supervision, is also important in text detection and recognition [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] . It's mainly used in word [CITATION_4] or character [CITATION_5] , [CITATION_6] level annotations. Bootstrapping for word-box Rong et al. [CITATION_7] proposes to combine an FCN-based text detection network with Maximally Stable Extremal Region (MSER) features to generate new training instances annotated on box-level. First, they train an FCN, which predicts the probability of each pixel belonging to text. Then, MSER features are extracted from regions where the text confidence is high. Using single linkage criterion (SLC) based algorithms [CITATION_8] , [CITATION_9] , final prediction is made. [CITATION_10] . Code:",
